  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: 'Q1) How is the cost of an object calculated?

    Each item uses the ratio
    of materials stated per 1 Health Point(HP). A wooden box with 10 HP requires
    1 wood and 0.1 metal ration. So the total needed is 10x1 wood and 10 x0.1 metal.
    Stronger objects require more materials but have a lower "Rate of Decay" when
    attacked.


    Q2) How do I get more materials?

    Press ''Z'' to switch to
    your mining tool and go into the forest and Left-Click on interactable items.
    This adds would add them to your inventory.


    Q3) How do i know which are
    interactable objects?

    If you are facing the object and its name shows up
    on the sceen, it is interactable.


    Q4) How do I place an object?

    Select
    your item with the Scroll Wheel, then Middle-Click and hold. A preview" will
    appear. Position it how you want and then release to build.'
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
